export const UXDesignContainer = () => {
  return (
    <div>
    <h2>How do I use UX Design?</h2>
    <p>UX Design is a very broad field, and there are many different ways to use it. For me, it is a way to solve problems and create meaningful experiences for users. I use UX Design to create digital products that are easy to use and provide value to the users. I also use it to improve existing products and make them more user-friendly.</p>
    <p>In my projects, I always start with research to understand the users and their needs. I then create wireframes and prototypes to test my ideas and get feedback from users. Finally, I work on the visual design and development of the product.</p>
  
    <h2>Why is UX Design the <i>better</i> it project management approach?</h2>
    <p>UX Design is a user-centered approach to product development, which means that it focuses on the needs and goals of the users. This is in contrast to traditional project management approaches, which often focus on the technical aspects of the project and the deliverables. By focusing on the users, UX Design can create products that are more likely to be successful and provide value to the users.</p>
    <p>UX Design also emphasizes collaboration and iteration, which allows for more flexibility and adaptability in the development process. This can lead to faster development times and better products.</p>
  
    <h2>How did my career path lead to me becoming an UX Designer?</h2>
    <p>My career path to becoming a UX Designer was not a straight line. I started out studying psychology, which gave me a strong understanding of human behavior and cognition. I then worked in various roles in the tech industry, including project management and product management. Through these roles, I became interested in the user experience and how to create products that are more user-friendly. I decided to pursue a career in UX Design and have been working in the field ever since.</p>
    </div>
  );
}
